Lancashire, England":"Yealand Conyers, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Yeland","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Normand, Armand, Andre, Aurore, Cecile, Donat, Emilien, Gaetan, Laurent, Lucienne, Marcel, Stephane.","French (<b>Béland</b>): variant of   Berland  . This surname is very rare in France. Compare   Belan  ,   Belland  ,   Bellow  , and   Bellows  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Berland","meanings":["French: from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>ber</i> ‘bear’ + <i>land</i> ‘country’.","Norwegian: habitational name from any of numerous farms in southwestern Norway named Berland, from Old Norse <i>bjarg</i> ‘mountain, hill’ or <i>ber</i> ‘berry’ + <i>land</i> ‘(piece of) land, farmstead’.","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): variant of <b>Brillant</b>, an artificial name from Yiddish <i>barlyant</i> ‘diamond, jewel’; compare   Brilliant  ."]},{"name":"Belland","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Antoine, Michel, Andre.","French: variant of <b>Béland</b> (see   Beland  ) and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this.","Norwegian: habitational name from any of the farmsteads in Agder so named, from an unexplained first element + <i>land</i> ‘land’."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Bright’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice de Yeland was born in 1216, in Yealand Conyers, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Sir Adam de Yealand, was 56 and her mother, Helewise de Lancaster, was 56. She had at least 1 son with Geoffrey Conyers. She died in 1276, at the age of 60."},"et":{"Abt 1216–Aft 1276":"1216–1276","1216–1276":"1216–1276","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1237–1299":"1237–1299","1160–1233":"1160–1233","1160–Female":"1160–Surnud","1216":"1216","1237":"1237","Aft 1276":"1276","Aft 1233":"1233","1233":"1233","1299":"1299","1200":"1200","1276":"1276","Abt 1216":"1216","1160":"1160","Sockburn, Durham, England":"Sockburn, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cowburn in Warton, Fylde, Lancashire, England":"Fylde, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Yealand Conyers, Lancashire, England":"Yealand Conyers, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1216–Aft 1276":"1216–1276","1216–1276":"1216–1276","1200–Male":"1200–Kuollut","1237–1299":"1237–1299","1160–1233":"1160–1233","1160–Female":"1160–Kuollut","1216":"1216","1237":"1237","Aft 1276":"1276","Aft 1233":"1233","1233":"1233","1299":"1299","1200":"1200","1276":"1276","Abt 1216":"1216","1160":"1160","Sockburn, Durham, England":"Sockburn, Durham, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cowburn in Warton, Fylde, Lancashire, England":"Fylde, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Yealand Conyers, Lancashire, England":"Yealand Conyers, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1216–Aft 1276":"1216–1276","1216–1276":"1216–1276","1200–Male":"1200–Décédé","1237–1299":"1237–1299","1160–1233":"1160–1233","1160–Female":"